# Donation-process component patterns

Applies to facility requests, admin review, browse, reference screens, etc.

---

## Scope — do not over-build

- Implement **only** what the task asks; no defensive extract/map layers for guessed API shapes.
- Confirm response shape from **docs** (`Docs/donation-process-api.md`) or **one console log**, then parse in the **service**.
- Components: load → store raw → build maps → `refreshDisplay()`. Match **`facility-requests-list`**.

---

## Lookups (types, categories, statuses)

Reference: `facility-requests-list.component.ts`

```ts
// Types / statuses from list API
this.rawTypes = Object.values(results.types.message ?? {}) as DonationTypeBackend[];
this.statuses = Object.values(results.statuses.message ?? {});

// Categories — load per type, merge
forkJoin(mappedTypes.map((t) => listDonationCategories(t.id, false))).subscribe(...)
```

**Details output keys** (when not flat indexed dict): unwrap in service — e.g. `Donation_Request`, `Donation_Types`, `Donation_Categories`, `History` via `donation-reference.service` / `donation-requests.service` extractors.

---

## Type label when details omit `Donation_Type_ID`

Details API often has `Donation_Category_ID` only. When loading categories per type, **stamp** parent type on each row if API omits it:

```ts
items.forEach((item) => {
  this.rawCategories.push({
    ...item,
    Donation_Type_ID: Number(item.Donation_Type_ID || typeId),
  });
});
```

Resolve type for display: `details.donationTypeId` or `categoryTypeIdById[donationCategoryId]`.

---

## Details / list display

| Data | Pattern |
|------|---------|
| Status, type, category labels | Label maps + `pickLocalizedField` (reference convention) |
| Request title, description, address | `pickRequestContentField` in `mapDonationRequestDetails` or list `getTitle()` |
| Workflow timeline | Parent passes pre-localized `workflowItems`; timeline is display-only |

---

## Services own parsing and mapping

- `mapDonationRequestDetails`, `mapDonationRequestWorkflow`, `mapDonationTypes`, … — use `pickLocalizedField` only for **reference** fields.
- `extractDonationRequestDetails`, `extractWorkflowHistory`, `extractDonationTypes` — live in services, not duplicated in components.

